        "schemeImageUrl": "",
        "detailedDescription_md": "The scheme &amp;quot;To Increase Fish Seed Production and Inland Fisheries Equipment in Non-Tribal Areas&amp;quot; introduced by the Agriculture, Farmers Welfare and Cooperation Department, Gujarat, aims to enhance fish seed production and promote inland fisheries in non-tribal areas. It provides financial assistance for fish farming, fish seed rearing, and procurement of essential fisheries equipment, benefiting individuals, societies, and self-help groups involved in inland fisheries.\n",
        "benefits_md": "<br>\n\n**Component Name****Standard of Assistance**\t**Minimum Time Limit for Reclaiming Benefits**Fish Seed Rearing\t₹90/- per 1000 (spawn to fry) ₹260/- per 1000 (fry to fingerlings) ₹460/- per 1000 (spawn to fingerlings)\t1 YearFish Seed/Prawn Seed Stocking\t50% subsidy on cost and transportation\t1 YearBoat &amp;amp;amp;amp; Net Assistance\t50% subsidy up to ₹7,500/- for Tin Boat-Net, ₹15,000/- for FRP Boat-Net\t6 YearsAssistance to Backward Women for Fish Sale Equipment\t50% subsidy up to ₹7,500/-\tOnce in a LifetimePlastic Crates\t50% subsidy up to ₹600/- per unit\t5 YearsAerator Assistance\t50% subsidy up to ₹50,000/-\t5 YearsFish Collection cum Patrolling Boat\t50% subsidy up to ₹2,50,000/-\tOnce in a LifetimeInsulated Box\t50% subsidy, up to ₹15,000/-\t5 YearsFish Cage Culture\t40% subsidy (General) up to ₹1,20,000/- 60% subsidy (SC/ST) up to ₹1,80,000/-\t3 YearsAssistance to Pagadia Fishermen\t90% subsidy up to ₹13,500/-\t3 YearsNew Fish Pond Construction\t40% subsidy (General) up to ₹2,80,000/- 60% (SC/ST) up to ₹4,20,000/-\tOnce in a LifetimeInput Assistance\t40% subsidy (General) up to ₹60,000/- 60% (SC/ST) up to ₹90,000/-\tOnce in a LifetimeMobile Laboratory Van\t50% subsidy up to ₹5,00,000/-\tOnce in a LifetimeFish Seed Hatchery\t50% subsidy up to ₹12,50,000/-\tOnce in a Lifetime<br>\n\n",
        "exclusions_md": "<br>\n\n",
        "briefDescription": "This scheme has been introduced by the Agriculture, Farmers Welfare and Cooperation Department, Gujarat. It aims to enhance fish seed production and promote inland fisheries in non-tribal areas.",
        "detailedDescription": [
          {
            "type": "align_justify",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "The scheme \"To Increase Fish Seed Production and Inland Fisheries Equipment in Non-Tribal Areas\" introduced by the Agriculture, Farmers Welfare and Cooperation Department, Gujarat, aims to enhance fish seed production and promote inland fisheries in non-tribal areas. It provides financial assistance for fish farming, fish seed rearing, and procurement of essential fisheries equipment, benefiting individuals, societies, and self-help groups involved in inland fisheries."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
